- main_bulb: Main Load (lamp) [inside enclosure: cube_load]
- internal_bulb: Internal Indicator Lamp [inside enclosure: cube_load] [NOTE: This lamp is connected in parallel with the main load and reflects voltage conditions across that branch.]
- load_diode: Load Protection Diode [inside enclosure: cube_load]
- load_cable_pos: Load Input Cable (+)
- load_cable_neg: Load Input Cable (−)

Instruction: Reconnect the 12 V source (preferably the battery pack), and with the cubes accessible, place the multimeter COM lead on the PSU Output Cable (−) where it exits the power supply module. Then probe, one by one, (1) the PSU Output Cable (+), (2) the battery pack positive terminal, and (3) the battery pack negative terminal, recording the DC voltage in each case. This will verify the actual polarity and reference for all previous measurements and determine whether the battery pack terminals are reversed or the meter has been using an incorrect reference point.
